  <title>Can I edit (and other questions relating to) the Part-Outline?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>How to...<keyword>Edit the Part Outline?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Can I edit (and other questions relating to) the Part-Outline?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:220px; height:146px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-Part-in-Mechanism-Editor.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Part-Outline in the Graphic-Area]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I Edit the Part-Outline?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Interface2">No. </text>The <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> is the symbol for the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> element.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">What do I do with a Part-Outline?</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">You also click, or double-click, the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> to edit the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">It is the symbol of the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> that you select to complete other commands; for example: Add <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I change the size of the Part-Outline symbol?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">YES</text><text styleclass="BodyText BI">.</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> Use the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Application-Settings" anchor="App-Access" styleclass="T_Menu">Application Settings &gt; Accessibility tab &gt; Graphic &gt; Symbol Display Size</link></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Must I display Part-Outlines in the graphic-area?</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">NO.</text> To hide <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outlines</text>, see <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Filters" styleclass="T_Menu">Display Filters &gt; Show/Hide Part-Outlines</link>.</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">However, you must show <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outlines</text> to <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Forces-Show-Force-Vectors">Display Force-Vectors</link></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">If you do not show <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outlines</text>, you can Double-Click the <text styleclass="VariableName">Y-axis</text> to edit a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I hide individual Part-Outlines?</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-indent">No.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
